channel.title: Portforwarding Not working at all!?
channel.description:
Hey everyone , im very sure that i've portforwarded correctly , it still wouldn't work so then i try'ed UTorrent to open the port up , then i try'ed connecting to my server again , then it still didn't work also iv'e checked the listening ports and there 43594 so i don't see whats up with it :S My internet provider is Sky.
Hope you guys can help!

item.title: Portforwarding Not working at all!?
item.dc:creator: @DannyIsSoPro DannyIsSoPro
item.description:
@DannyIsSoPro wrote:

You can’t forward your ports with Utorrent, it doesn’t work with RSPS, atleast. I’ve tried many times; just contact your ISP(Sky) and ask them to open up the port you want opened up.
